title: New York posting weekly fall foliage reports
text:
ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) â€” New York state has begun posting its fall foliage reports.
The foliage reports can be accessed through the I Love New York tourism web site. They chart color conditions across the state and will be updated every Wednesday through the end of autumn.
Current reports from volunteer leaf peepers show some color emerging the in the Adirondacks, the Catskills and other areas. But leaves remain green around much of the state.
The 2015 fall foliage report is available at www.ILOVENY.com/fall.
